{
  "name": "nti-2-open-systems-1dd3af",
  "title": "Open Systems: A Technology Status Report",
  "description": "This Aberdeen Group workbook provides a comprehensive status report on Open Systems as of January 1993, covering the transition from proprietary to open, distributed computing architectures. It assesses five key technology components \u2014 hardware microprocessors, systems software, application development toolsets, networking, and emerging architectures \u2014 and profiles major vendor positions and standards organizations. The study culminates in an ACTION framework for IS executives managing the organizational and economic challenges of open systems adoption.",
